cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a novel architecture for Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) to improve accuracy without input data transmutation. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of dropout and orthonormal initialization to overcome training difficulties, which are common topics in neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper demonstrates its classification performance on the MNIST dataset, which is a common benchmark dataset in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
